
BellSouth has turned to Yahoo for help boosting the company's high-speed Internet service. BellSouth on Monday announced is the latest company to sign a deal to offer digital subscriber line service, or DSL, under a co-branding arrangement with Yahoo. Verizon and SBC are among those that have previously announced such deals. Simply put, new BellSouth DSL customers will, starting in late 2006, begin their service with a new Yahoo/BellSouth set as a default home page. Existing customers will be able to shift to the co-branded service as well. 

